Relationships between trait and state anxiety and the central benzodiazepine receptor: a PET study. The central benzodiazepine receptor (cBZr) has long been implicated in anxiety disorders on the basis of: (i) the well-known anxiolytic and anxiogenic properties of cBZr agonists and inverse agonists, respectively (ii) a possibly reduced sensitivity to benzodiazepines in anxious subjects